The First Lady of the United States, Jill Biden, addressed Olympians and Paralympians at the White House. She expressed her gratitude for their performances at the Games in Japan and shared her excitement for the three-on-three women's basketball game she watched. Biden highlighted the power of sports to bring people together, transcend differences, and inspire belief in the impossible. She acknowledged the challenges the athletes faced due to the global pandemic and commended their achievements. Biden concluded by expressing pride in the athletes and thanking them for the hope, joy, unity, and inspiration they have provided.